			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: What songs?<a name="11527"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 29 03 9:52 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Bards are all about fitting the situation.  If you are soloing, then charm, dot, or AE kiting tips are all over this board.
<br />
If you are grouping, then take a look at 3 things to determine what songs you twist.
<br />
#1 What is the group composition.  
<br />
  Some songs we will always sing.  Mana and Haste are always in the twist in most exp groups.  You may toss in erjav or some other stacking melee buff, but at 60 I usually used a Psalm line of resist/DS.
<br />
   Chanters, Shaman, and BL haste and slow, if you dont have any of then in group, you will have to do it.  (Our song haste is better then BL haste at this level I believe)
<br />
   Chanters crowd control, if there is no chanter, you need to do it.
<br />
   You may be the puller, if so, it doesnt adjust your battle twist, it just means that you start it a little later.
<br />
    You can be totally successful in a group with no shaman, BL, or chanter.  You can pull, haste, slow and mezz if you have to.  All we really need in a group is a healer and a tank.  Toss in any other 3 classes and you can rock.
<br />

<br />
#2  Where will you be adventuring/EXPing? 
<br />
  Some songs are more effective agianst certain mobs, some resists are needed in certain areas or against certain mobs.   Some groups need different things, base your twist on your group and where they are hunting.
<br />

<br />
#3  how busy do you want to be ;o)   You dont HAVE to instrument swap, you dont HAVE to melee, you dont HAVE to twist 4 songs, you dont HAVE to pull, you dont HAVE to slow mobs on inc....  Base what you do on your other group members.  There are times when you MAKE the group, and there are times when you can sit back, sing mana, and melee your little heart out.
<br />

<br />

<br />
All this is predicated on the idea that you know your songs.  If you dont know your song and what they do, then look em up here and learn. </span></td>
