				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: What songs?<a name="18955"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 4 04 3:10 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Like someone posted somewhere earlier... I cant recall where...
<br />

<br />
The songs we use regularly can be counted on 2 hands, the other 90% of our songs are situational or never used.
<br />

<br />
Only way to know what to use, where to use it and when to use it is by trying, failing and learning.
<br />

<br />
What makes a good Bard isnt how good he is at twisting 4 songs. Its how good he is to play the right songs in the right situations.
<br />

<br />
IE. Song of Highsun, most think its a play-around song only used for fun.
<br />

<br />
Song of Highsun is essential during the 10th Ring war in Great Divide, since bards can chase down runners and simply gate them away from Thurgadin.
<br />

<br />
Just an example of situational uses.
<br />

<br />
A bad use of Highsun, would be to gate away a roamer add in LDoN instead of mezzing/offtanking it. If you dont have DA song, Mana for Fade or an evac'er then I'd suggest running... =PP
<br />

<br />
Try, fail, learn.... nuff said!~</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">Enadil Elvensinger
